result.name: organogram-hm-revenue-and-customs
result.notes:
Organogram (organisation chart) showing all staff roles. Names and salaries are also listed for the Senior Civil Servants.

Organogram data is released by all central government departments and their agencies since 2010. Snapshots for 31 March and 30 September were published on a 6-monthly basis each year up until 2021, since when snapshots for 31 March, 30 June, 30 September and 31 December are published quarterly. The published data is validated and released in CSV format and OGL-licensed for reuse. For more information about this series, see: http://guidance.data.gov.uk/organogram-data.html

Click Preview next to a dataset to view interactive visualisations of the data.

organization.description:
What we do

We are the UK’s tax authority. We are responsible for making sure that the money is available to fund the UK’s public services and for helping families and individuals with targeted financial support.

HMRC is a non-ministerial department, supported by 2 agencies and public bodies.
